headline: Review & Preview: Inflation Relief Rally
summary: All three indexes notched new records today, spurred higher by a much-awaited inflation report that came in cooler than expected.  The Dow Jones Industrial Average rose 1%, closing north of 47,000 for the first time ever.  Caterpillar, IBM, and Apple were the biggest contributors to the current 1,000-point increase, while Home Depot, Sherwin-Williams, and Travelers Cos. subtracted the most, according to Dow Jones Market Data.

headline: Stock Market Today: Dow, S&P 500, Nasdaq Close At New Highs On Cool CPI Data
summary: The Dow Jones Industrial Average and other major indexes posted healthy gains Friday after a lower-than-expected inflation report.  IBM soared 7.9% and helped lift the Dow, as well as chipmaker Advanced Micro Devices.  All three major indexes got a boost as the U.S. Consumer Price Index readout came in softer than expected, paving the way for more interest rate cuts.

headline: IBM and Google Are Also Making Moves in Quantum. Don’t Count Out the Bigger Players.
summary: International Business Machines  said Friday that it had used hardware from  Advanced Micro Devices  to run a quantum-error correction algorithm, representing a step toward building “practical and realistic” hybrid systems.  Shares of IBM climbed 7.5% following the announcement, putting the stock on pace for its largest percentage increase since January, according to Dow Jones Market Data.  Earlier this year, IBM unveiled a road map to building a fault-tolerant quantum computer, or a machine that can catch and correct errors as they occur.

headline: IBM (IBM): Earnings vs. Bull Narratives
summary: International Business Machines (IBM) reported net profit margins of 12.1%, up from 10.2% last year, with earnings growing at an impressive 24.3% over the past year and averaging 14% per year over the last five years. Earnings are projected to grow at 8.6% annually moving forward, while revenue is expected to increase at 4.7% per year, lagging behind the broader US market. Investors will need to weigh the improved margins and continued profit growth against slower forward expectations.
